alexis charles the clayman institute for gender research skip to main content standford university the clayman institute for gender research the clayman institute for gender research home programs news strategic focus events about research fellowships library media center gender news no news found events no events found you are here home people alexis charles alexis charles graduate student modern thought & literature alexis charles is a doctoral candidate in the modern thought & literature program at stanford her dissertation focuses on history and memory in contemporary black popular culture examining how black artists assemble alternative feminist futures from historical social and political constructions of blackness bringing together feminist oral history black feminist theory visual culture theory and techniques of literary analysis her work examines rock posters book covers popular music and black science fiction literature from the 1990s through the present alexis also works at the stanford women's community center as a graduate program coordinator and is a co founder and facilitator of the graduate student creative writing workshop sponsored by the vpge donate make a donation social links facebook twitter youtube scribd contact serra house 589 capistrano way stanford ca 94305 8640 map 650 723 1994 gender email stanford edu
